‚úÖ Final Working Setup: Hercules + z/OS + TUN/TAP + Clean Internet
üîß 1. Ensure TUN/TAP is enabled on Linux

ls /dev/net/tun

If it doesn't exist:

sudo mkdir -p /dev/net
sudo mknod /dev/net/tun c 10 200
sudo chmod 666 /dev/net/tun

Check kernel has TUN:

sudo modprobe tun
dmesg | grep tun

üîß 2. Correct your Hercules network config

Edit your config file (e.g., s390.CONF) and make sure you use only this line for LCS:

0E20.2 LCS -n /dev/net/tun

Don't add IPs or use tap0 directly.
üß† 3. Edit your z/OS TCP/IP PROFILE

Use this full config (this is the final, corrected version):

DEVICE LCS1   LCS E20 AUTORESTART
LINK   ETH1   ETHERNET 0 LCS1
HOME   192.168.4.150 ETH1

ROUTE 192.168.4.0    255.255.255.0   =         ETH1   MTU DEFAULTSIZE
ROUTE DEFAULT        192.168.4.250               ETH1   MTU DEFAULTSIZE

START LCS1
ENDRoutes

    .150 = z/OS IP

    .250 = Linux TAP gateway IP (we‚Äôll assign this next)

üíª 4. Start Hercules as root

sudo hercules -f /path/to/s390.CONF

You should see:

HHC00901I 0:0E20 LCS: Interface tap0, type TAP opened

üåê 5. Configure tap0 on the Linux host

Set the TAP interface to a non-conflicting IP (e.g., .250):

sudo ip link set tap0 up
sudo ip addr del 192.168.4.1/24 dev tap0  # only if previously assigned
sudo ip addr add 192.168.4.250/24 dev tap0

Verify:

ip addr show tap0

You should see:

inet 192.168.4.250/24 scope global tap0

üîÅ 6. Recycle z/OS TCP/IP stack

From SDSF or console:

P TCPIP
S TCPIP

Check with:

NETSTAT HOME
PING 192.168.4.250

üì∂ 7. Test connectivity

From Linux:

ping 192.168.4.150

From z/OS:

PING 192.168.4.250

Both directions should work flawlessly.
‚úÖ 8. (Optional) Enable Internet Access for z/OS (if desired)

sudo sysctl -w net.ipv4.ip_forward=1
sudo iptables -t nat -A POSTROUTING -o wlp3s0 -j MASQUERADE

Replace wlp3s0 with your real internet interface (ip route shows this).
üßº 9. (Optional) Disable IP forwarding/NAT if you don‚Äôt need internet

sudo iptables -t nat -D POSTROUTING -o wlp3s0 -j MASQUERADE
sudo sysctl -w net.ipv4.ip_forward=0

üéâ Done!

You now have:

    Full z/OS ‚Üî Linux networking via TAP

    Clean, conflict-free IP setup

    No internet slowdown

    Optional z/OS outbound internet (if enabled)



